Supermarket Sales Data Analysis
Step 1: Import Libraries
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
Explanation
Pandas is used to read and analyze the dataset.
Matplotlib is used to create charts and graphs.
Step 2: Load the Dataset
df = pd.read_csv("supermarket_sales.csv")
Explanation

Reads the CSV file and stores it in a DataFrame for analysis.

Step 3: View the Dataset
print(df.head(10))
print(df.tail(10))
Explanation
head(10) displays the first 10 rows.
tail(10) displays the last 10 rows.

Purpose:
To understand the structure of the dataset.

Step 4: Check Dataset Size
print(df.shape)
print(df.columns)
Explanation
shape returns the total number of rows and columns.
columns displays all column names.

Purpose:
To know the dimensions of the dataset.

Step 5: Check Data Types
print(df.dtypes)
Explanation

Shows the data type of every column (integer, float, object, etc.).

Purpose:
To understand the type of data stored in each column.

Step 6: Check Missing Values
print(df.isnull().sum())
Explanation

Counts the missing values in each column.

Purpose:
To identify incomplete data.

Step 7: Fill Missing Values
numeric_columns = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).columns

for col in numeric_columns:
    df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].mean())
Explanation

Replaces missing values in numerical columns with the column mean.

Purpose:
To make the dataset complete before analysis.

Step 8: Remove Duplicate Values
df = df.drop_duplicates()
Explanation

Removes duplicate rows from the dataset.

Purpose:
To improve data quality.

Step 9: Convert Date Format
df["Date"] = pd.to_datetime(df["Date"])
Explanation

Converts the Date column into datetime format.

Purpose:
To perform date-based analysis.

Step 10: Create Month Column
df["Month"] = df["Date"].dt.month_name()
Explanation

Extracts the month name from the Date column.

Purpose:
To analyze monthly sales.

Step 11: Create Revenue Column
df["Revenue"] = df["Total"]
Explanation

Creates a new Revenue column using the Total sales amount.

Purpose:
To simplify revenue analysis.

Step 12: Monthly Revenue Analysis
monthly_revenue = df.groupby("Month")["Revenue"].sum()
Explanation

Calculates the total revenue for each month.

Purpose:
To compare monthly sales performance.

Step 13: Line Chart
plt.plot(...)
Explanation

Displays monthly revenue using a line chart.

Purpose:
To show revenue trends over time.

Step 14: Product Line Analysis
product_sales = df.groupby("Product line")["Revenue"].sum()
Explanation

Calculates total revenue generated by each product line.

Purpose:
To identify the best-selling product category.

Step 15: Bar Chart
plt.bar(...)
Explanation

Shows revenue for each product line using bars.

Purpose:
To compare product categories visually.

Step 16: Payment Method Analysis
payment_counts = df["Payment"].value_counts()
Explanation

Counts how many customers used each payment method.

Purpose:
To identify the most popular payment option.

Step 17: Pie Chart
plt.pie(...)
Explanation

Displays the percentage of each payment method.

Purpose:
To visualize payment method distribution.

Step 18: Customer Type Distribution
customer_counts = df["Customer type"].value_counts()
Explanation

Counts the number of customers in each customer type.

Purpose:
To compare member and normal customers.

Step 19: Customer Type Bar Chart
plt.bar(...)
Explanation

Displays customer distribution using a bar chart.

Purpose:
To compare customer categories.

Step 20: Quantity Histogram
plt.hist(...)
Explanation

Shows the frequency of purchased quantities.

Purpose:
To understand the distribution of sales quantity.

Step 21: Scatter Plot
plt.scatter(df["Quantity"], df["Revenue"])
Explanation

Shows the relationship between Quantity and Revenue.

Purpose:
To analyze whether higher quantities generate higher revenue.
